@Madlohe thanks for taking a look!
Yes, I implemented all these fixes because some performance data were missing in our setup (which is Icinga 2 + Graphite + Grafana), and there were messages in logs complaining about the units.
If some systems do not care and do work well with non-standard units, I think the plugin could have an "extended" mode, activated with a switch, to provide these units (if that's really important), but the operation should be according to the specs by default IMHO.

The code on the current maint branch doesn't solve the problem.  It still tries and fails to import utf8::all when it is not available.  This change should solve the issue with and without the module available:
diff --git i/plugins-scripts/check_disk_smb.pl w/plugins-scripts/check_disk_smb.pl
index fa99a361..63617156 100755
--- i/plugins-scripts/check_disk_smb.pl
+++ w/plugins-scripts/check_disk_smb.pl
@@ -19,10 +19,7 @@
 #

 require 5.004;
-eval "use utf8::all";
-if ( $@ ) {
-    use utf8::all;
-}
+eval { require utf8::all; };
 use POSIX;
 use strict;
 use Getopt::Long;
I tested this by adding print("$utf8::all::VERSION\n"); to confirm that the module had been imported on systems where the utf8::all module is installed.  I couldn't come up with a more thorough way to test the module had been imported and would do what it intended after a quick look at the module's documentation.

